{"id":898,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":253,"title":"Cam5 - Test 4 - Part 1","subtitle":"Host Family Placement Interview","level":"B1","parts":68,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam5-test-4-part-1.898/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/0-ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Good morning, how can I help you?\nGood morning.\nI understand you help fix up students with host families.\nThat's right...\nare you interested in...?\nWell please sit down and I'll just take a few details.\nThank you.\nRight, now... what name is it?\nJenny Chan.\nCan you spell that please?\nYes...\nJENNY\nCHAN.\nRight... and what is your present address?\nSea View Guest House, 14 Hill Road.\nOkay, and do you know the phone number there?\nYes... I have it here...\n2237676\nbut I'm only there after about 7 pm.\nSo when would be the best time to catch you?\nI suppose between 9 and, let me see, half-past, before I leave for the college.\nGreat... and can I ask you your age?\nI've just had my nineteenth birthday.\nAnd how long would you want to stay with the host family?\nI'm planning on staying a year\nbut at the moment I'm definitely here for four months only.\nI have to get an extension to my permit.\nYou're working on it?\nFine...\nand what will be your occupation while you're in the UK?\nStudying English?\nAnd what would you say your level of English is?\nGood, I think.\nI'd like to say 'advanced' but my written work is below the level of my spoken,\nso I suppose it's intermediate.\nCertainly your spoken English is advanced.\nAnyway, which area do you think you would prefer?\nWell, I'm studying right in the centre\nbut I'd really like to live in the north-west.\nThat shouldn't be a great problem...\nwe usually have lots of families up there...\nAnd do you have any particular requirements for diet?\nWell, I'm nearly a vegetarian... not quite.\nShall I say you are? It's probably easier that way.\nThat would be best.\nAnything about your actual room?\nI would prefer my own facilities - 'en suite', is that right?\nAnd also if it's possible, a TV\nand I'd also like the house to have a real garden rather than just a yard,\nsomewhere I could sit and be peaceful.\nIs that all?\nWell... I'm really serious about improving my English\nso I'd prefer to be the only guest if that's possible?\nNo other guests...\nYes, you get more practice that way.\nAnyway, obviously all this is partly dependent on how much you're willing to pay.\nWhat did you have in mind?\nI was thinking in terms of about £60 to £80 a week,\nbut I'd go up to a hundred if it was something special.\nWell, I don't think we'd have any problems finding something for you.\nOh, good.\nAnd when would you want it for?\nI'd like to move in approximately two weeks.\nLet me see, it's the 10th today...\nso if we go for the Monday it's the 23rd of March.\nYes.\nRight...\ngood, and if I could ask one last question...","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:40","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Good morning, how can I help you?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/1.mp3","time_start":0.51,"time_end":2.63},{"position":2,"content":"Good morning.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/2.mp3","time_start":2.63,"time_end":3.8},{"position":3,"content":"I understand you help fix up students with host families.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/3.mp3","time_start":4.54,"time_end":9.08},{"position":4,"content":"That's right...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/4.mp3","time_start":9.08,"time_end":10.33},{"position":5,"content":"are you interested in...?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/5.mp3","time_start":10.33,"time_end":12.85},{"position":6,"content":"Well please sit down and I'll just take a few details.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/6.mp3","time_start":13.05,"time_end":16.57},{"position":7,"content":"Thank you.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/7.mp3","time_start":16.57,"time_end":17.58},{"position":8,"content":"Right, now... what name is it?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/8.mp3","time_start":17.93,"time_end":20.54},{"position":9,"content":"Jenny Chan.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/9.mp3","time_start":20.54,"time_end":21.9},{"position":10,"content":"Can you spell that please?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/10.mp3","time_start":21.9,"time_end":23.55},{"position":11,"content":"Yes...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/11.mp3","time_start":23.55,"time_end":24.43},{"position":12,"content":"JENNY","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/12.mp3","time_start":24.43,"time_end":28.76},{"position":13,"content":"CHAN.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-5-test-4-part-1-2023-08-09-22-33-54/13.mp3","time_start":29.21,"time_end":31.85},{"position":14,"content":"Right... and what is your present address?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambrid